    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Goals and Recommendations\n Shopper Copilot for Commerce Stores\n Shopper Copilot and Your Data\n Set Up Shopper Copilot for a B2B or D2C Store\n Set Up Shopper Copilot for a B2C Store\n Create a Bot in Your Commerce Store\n Connect and Train Your Bot to Support Shopper Copilot\n Customize a Bot for a Commerce Store\n Configure a Store Catalog Description to Support Shopper Copilot\n Create a Customized Shopper Copilot Bot for B2B or D2C\n Create a Customized Shopper Copilot Bot for B2C\n Adjust Order Numbers for Content Migrated to Shopper Copilot for B2B...\n Get Help with Store Issues with the Troubleshooting Assistant\n Using Salesforce CMS for Product Media\n Assign a CMS Public Channel to a Commerce Store\n Commerce Workspaces\n Migrate Your Store Configuration\n Commerce Analytics\n Create Custom Reports with Search and Category Data for B2B Stores\n Manage Integrations for Your Store\n Set Up Inventory for Commerce Stores\n Replace a Default Commerce Process with an Apex Class\n Create Email Order Confirmation Notifications\n Configure What Shoppers or Buyers See When a Store Isn’t Available\n Commerce Promotions\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nConfigure a Store Catalog Description to Support Shopper Copilot\n\nThe bot can use the store catalog description to generate product recommendations based on a customer’s query.\n\nClick  at the top of the page, and then select Setup.\nIn the Quick Find box, enter Process Automation, and then select Flows.\nSelect Concierge Bots for B2B or D2C: Get Product Recommendations or Concierge Bots for B2C: Get Product Recommendations.\nIn the flow, click the Get Product Recommendation action element.\nClick Edit Element.\nUpdate the Web Store Description field using up to 4,000 characters.\nAdd categories such as Games, Electronics, and Accessories to a catalog description. You don’t receive an error if your description exceeds 4,000 characters, but the recommendation stops working.\nClick Save As.\nClick New Version.\nClick Save.\nIn the Bot Builder, from the Bot Builder menu, select Dialogs.\nSelect Product Recommendations Block, and click Get Product Recommendations.\nSelect the Action element.\nReplace the inputs and outputs with the following name variables.\nSave your changes.\nClick Activate.\nTo test some queries and check whether they cover the information that you want your customers to receive, go to Preview in your Bot Builder, and select Test Preview .\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
